    • Method Detail

      • setName

        public void setName​(java.lang.String name)
        Sets the name of the injection target. Corresponds to the injection-target-name element in the deployment descriptor.

        For field injection, this is the field name. For method injection, this is the JavaBeans property name corresponding to the setter method (the method name without the "set" prefix and with the first character lowercased).

        Parameters:
        name - the injection target name (field name or property name)
        See Also:
        Servlet 4.0 Specification, Section 14.5.1: Injection Target

      • getName

        public java.lang.String getName()
        Returns the name of the injection target.
        Returns:
        the injection target name

      • setClassName

        public void setClassName​(java.lang.String className)
        Sets the fully-qualified class name of the target class. Corresponds to the injection-target-class element in the deployment descriptor.

        This is the class that contains the field or setter method where the resource will be injected.

        Parameters:
        className - the fully-qualified class name of the injection target class
        See Also:
        Servlet 4.0 Specification, Section 14.5.1: Injection Target

      • getClassName

        the injection target class name
